In smart contract verification scripts, IRWAToken404 interface ABI doesn't include inherited methods like supportsInterface from ERC165. Always use the full RWAToken404 contract ABI (artifacts/contracts/core/RWAToken404.sol/RWAToken404.json) instead of interface ABI for testing inherited functionality.
When verifying ERC404 contract interface support, actually call supportsInterface() on the deployed contract instead of assuming interfaces are supported based on inheritance. Use interface IDs: ERC20='0x36372b07', ERC721='0x80ac58cd', ERC721Metadata='0x5b5e139f'.
RWAToken404 contract properly implements ERC165 supportsInterface() and correctly advertises support for ERC20, ERC721, and ERC721Metadata interfaces. The contract inherits from ERC20 and manually implements ERC721 functions, with supportsInterface checking all three interface IDs.
